I Have addreed my alutes before, but hear they micarried. The labour to repeat them is not burthenom, yet let their loe might bring you into up • tion, that I was as ilent as their micarriage makes me eem, I add thee to try better fortune;
in which, if more happy, they know their errand, to preent me & my loves to your devotion. If they tammer in the delivery, they bet e •
pres my elf, whoe expreion (urcharg'd by your deerts) mut conceive more obligation, mother more affection, then I can utter. You can mend both by the clearnee of a candid interpretation, till both are able to be more articulate and plain; None can better expound gratitude, then he who mot merits it. Sir, I forget not the delights of your ingenious converations, thoe weet (but too hort) moments of my contents. I remember your ready favors, your reall endearments, I remember all, and for all am thankfull. Will you have more? More then this you cannot, I am (what I am)
